   {
      "body" : "Well usually QA instability is addressed by changing the tests, and I think we tend to be pretty liberal about backporting test changes.\r\n\r\nPersonally I think it makes sense to backport this behavior change, as I mentioned above I think this is basically a bugfix since it could be triggered in some mainnet configurations as well, and I think the patch here is small and low risk.  Not sure if everyone would agree with my assessment though...?",
